As regards the construction of ac- cessit, observe that it takes the accusative with or without ad, or else the dative. It takes the accusative with ad when a thing or person is actually reached3 the accusative without ad (as in the present instance), when the place or person is not immediately reached ; and the dative, when the place or person is more remote.
